s4uproxy.help: S4U proxy. SPN: spn format. targetuser: user@FQDN format

asreproast.help: ASREPRoast user. Target is expected in user@FQDN format !OR! Integer denoting an active LDAP client for automatic kerberoast.

nt.help: Gets NT hash from a PKINIT (cert) auth

cve202233679.help: Performs the CVE-2020-13379 attack. This attack will return a valid TGT for the current ASREProastable user if the domain is vulnerable.

targetenum.help: Grabs all computers in the domain and puts them in the targets window

userenum.help: Enumerates all users in the domain. This is only used in the game

dump.help: Fetches ALL user and machine accounts from the domain with a LOT of attributes

tree.help: Prints a tree from the given DN (if not set, the top) and with a given depth (default: 1)

query.help: Performs a raw LDAP query against the server.
query.extrahelp: Secondary parameter is the requested attributes SEPARATED WITH COMMA (,)

modify.help: Modify an attribute of object. Only works with string data types!

user.help: Feteches a user object based on the sAMAccountName of the user

adduser.help: Creates a new domain user with password

deluser.help: Deletes the user! This action is irrecoverable (actually domain admins can do that but probably will shout with you)

changeuserpw.help: Changes user password, if you are admin then old pw doesnt need to be supplied

unlockuser.help: Unlock user by setting lockoutTime to 0

enableuser.help: Unlock user by flipping useraccountcontrol bits

disableuser.help: Unlock user by flipping useraccountcontrol bits

addspn.help: Adds an SPN entry to the users account

delspn.help: Removes an SPN entry to the users account

addusertogroup.help: Adds user to specified group. Both user and group must be in DN format!

deluserfromgroup.help: Removes user from specified group. Both user and group must be in DN format!

machine.help: Feteches a machine object based on the sAMAccountName of the machine

addhostname.help: Adds additional hostname to computer account

pre2000.help: Lists potentially abusable machine accounts created with pre windows-2000 flag

changesamaccountname.help: Changes the sAMAccountName of a given DN

gpos.help: Lists all GPOs in the domain

groupmembership.help: Feteches names all groupnames the user is a member of for a given DN

groupmembers.help: Returns all member users in a group specified by DN

dadms.help: Lists all members of the domain administrators group

schemaentry.help: Feteches a schema object entry object based on the DN of the object (must start with CN=)

allschemaentry.help: Feteches all schema object entry objects

changeowner.help: Changes the owner in a Security Descriptor to the new_owner_sid on an LDAP object or on an LDAP object's attribute identified by target_dn and target_attribute. target_attribute can be omitted to change the target_dn's SD's owner

addprivdcsync.help: Adds DCSync rights to the given user by modifying the forest's Security Descriptor to add GetChanges and GetChangesAll ACE

addprivaddmember.help: Adds AddMember rights to the user on the group specified by group_dn

setsd.help: Updates the security descriptor of an object

getsd.help: Feteches security info for a given DN

addallowedtoactonbehalfofotheridentity.help: Adds a SID to the msDS-AllowedToActOnBehalfOfOtherIdentity protperty of target_dn

sidresolv.help: Returns the domain and username for a given SID

sid2dn.help: Returns the DN for a given SID

dn2sid.help: Returns the SID for a given DN

dn2sam.help: Fetches the sAMAccountName of an object based on the DN

sam2dn.help: Fetches the DN of an object based on the sAMAccountName

gmsa.help: Lists all managed service accounts (MSA). If user has permissions it retrieves the password as well

certify.help: Identifies all/vulnerable certificate templates (depending on cmd).
certify.extrahelp:
For vulnerable templates it will also list the reason why it is vulnerable
		Username is optional, if provided it will check if the specified user has permissions to interact with the template.

addcerttemplatenameflagaltname.help: Modifyies the msPKI-Certificate-Name-Flag value of the specified certificate template and enables ENROLLEE_SUPPLIES_SUBJECT_ALT_NAME bit. If 'flags' is present then it will assign that value.

addenrollmentright.help: Grants enrollment rights to a user (by DN) for the specified certificate template.

dnsdump.help: Enumerates all DNS records and writes them in a file

logout.help: Logs out from the current session, disconnects from the server

nodce.help: Disables automatic share listing on login

get.help: Download a file from the remote share to the current folder

put.help: Uploads a file to the remote share

del.help: Removes a file from the remote share

mkdir.help: Creates a directory on the remote share

getdirsd.help: Gets security descriptor for current directory

getfilesd.help: Gets security descriptor for a file in the current directory

refreshcurdir.help: Refreshes file list in current directory

enumall.help: Enumerates all shares for all files and folders recursively

groupmembers.help: Lists members of an arbitrary group

localgroupmembers.help: Lists members of a local group

addsidtolocalgroup.help: Add member (by SID) to a local group

servicedeploy.help: Deploys a binary file from the local system as a service on the remote system

reglistusers.help: Lists users who have ever logged in to this machine

regsave.help: Saves a registry hive to a file on remote share

printerenumdrivers.help: Enumerates all shares for all files and folders recursively

certreq.help: Requests a new certificate for the user specified in CN with altname
certreq.extrahelp:
service: name of the ADCS service without the domain part
template: name of the certificate template to use
cn: CN of the user (in username@fqdn format like: victim@test.corp)
altname: Alternative user to be included in the cert (in username@fqdn format like: Administrator@test.corp). Used for impersonatig a higher level user. (optional)

certreqonbehalf.help: Requests a new certificate for the user specified in CN with altname on behalf of the user specified in onbehalf

servicecmdexec.help: Executes a shell command as a service and returns the result

taskcmdexec.help: Executes a shell command using the scheduled tasks service

regdump.help: Dumps remote registry hives, parses them remotely, extracts secrets

regdump2.help: Extracts the secrets from the remote registry without touching the disk

backupkeys.help: Obtains the DPAPI domain backup keys

lsassdump.help: Dumps LSASS remotely, parses it to extract secrets

cpasswd.help: Searches SYSVOL for xml files containing cppasswords

printnightmare.help: printnightmare bug using the RPRN protocol

parprintnightmare.help: printnightmare bug using the PAR protocol

send.help: Sends a string encoded by 'encoding' to the socket

sendhex.help: Sends a hex-encoded binary data to the socket. WARNING! Doesn't add line terminator!

sendfile.help: Reads a file in blocksize and send it to the server

encoding.help: Sets or gets the text encoding for incoming and outgoing text data

lineterm.help: Sets or gets the line terminator for outgoing text data

binprint.help: Enables binary print. Incoming data will be printed as hexdump
binprint.extrahelp:
Use '1' to enable
Use '0' to disable

pastefile.help: Pushes text file content to remote clipboard

duckyexec.help: Starts ducky script. You'll need to login first!

duckyfile.help: Sets duckyscript file to use with duckyexec

screenshot.help: Take screenshot of remote desktop. You'll need to login first!

resolvfile.help: Resolve a list of hosts from a file

logout.help: Logs out from the current session, disconnects from the server

peerlist.help: Gets the list of peers currently connected to the NTP server
